OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 2 Mar to Wed 11 Mar
OL,6,FThis period will start with cloud,
OL,7,Frain and strong winds affecting
OL,8,Fnorthern and western parts of the UK
OL,9,Fon Monday. The cloud and rain is
OL,10,Fexpected to ease and clear to the
OL,11,Fsoutheast during Tuesday as high
OL,12,Fpressure builds in from the west.
OL,13,FThere is now a signal for high
OL,14,Fpressure to be largely dominant
OL,15,Fthrough the rest of this period. This
OL,16,Fwill mean many places seeing plenty of
OL,17,Fdry weather with variable cloud
OL,18,Famounts and some sunshine, but perhaps
OL,19,Fwith some fog overnight. Frontal
OL,20,Fsystems may still graze the north and
OL,21,Fwest of the UK at times though, maybe
OL,22,Falso briefly affecting other parts.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,FTemperatures will be near or above
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fnormal, although patchy overnight
OL,25,Ffrost is still likely at times.
